# Security rules — {{project_name}}

## Hard rules
- No secrets in code, commits, or logs — use environment variables or a secrets manager
- No `eval()` on user-supplied input
- No SQL string interpolation — always parameterized queries
- No `innerHTML` with user-supplied content
- All file paths from user input validated against an allowlist

## Every PR checklist
- [ ] Inputs validated and sanitized at the system boundary?
- [ ] Error messages safe to show users? (No stack traces, internal paths.)
- [ ] Does this touch auth/authz? If yes, flag for lead review before merge.
- [ ] New dependencies pinned and justified in the PR description?

## Dependency policy
- New runtime dependencies need a one-sentence justification
- Run `pip-audit` or `npm audit` before merging dependency changes

## Incident rule
If a secret is accidentally committed: rotate it immediately, then clean git history. Rotation first.

